methods.write:
Writes a table in parquet format under a given path

*Overload 1*  
  :param t: (io.deephaven.db.tables.Table) - The table to write
  :param path: (java.lang.String) - The destination path
  :param incomingMeta: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) - A map of metadata values to be stores in the file footer
  :param groupingPathFactory: (java.util.function.Function<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) - 
  :param groupingColumns: (java.lang.String...) - List of columns the tables are grouped by (the write operation will store the grouping info)
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param t: io.deephaven.db.tables.Table
  :param path: java.lang.String
  :param incomingMeta: java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
  :param groupingColumns: java.lang.String...
  
*Overload 3*  
  :param t: (io.deephaven.db.tables.Table) - The table to write
  :param definition: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) - Table definition
  :param writeInstructions: (io.deephaven.db.v2.parquet.ParquetInstructions) - Write instructions for customizations while writing
  :param destPathName: (java.lang.String) - The destination path
  :param incomingMeta: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) - A map of metadata values to be stores in the file footer
  :param groupingPathFactory: (java.util.function.Function<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) -

*Overload 4*

  :param groupingColumns: java.lang.String...
  
*Overload 5*  
  :param table: (io.deephaven.db.tables.Table) - The table to write
  :param definition: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) - The table definition
  :param writeInstructions: (io.deephaven.db.v2.parquet.ParquetInstructions) - Write instructions for customizations while writing
  :param path: (java.lang.String) - The destination path
  :param tableMeta: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) - A map of metadata values to be stores in the file footer
  :param tableInfoBuilder: (io.deephaven.db.v2.parquet.metadata.TableInfo.Builder) - A partially-constructed builder for the metadata object
